CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1953, pg. 10, reads: "Spreading Sunshine and Cheer - A group of Omega Grand Chapter's energetic members got together recently to prepare baskets for the residents of Woodville County Hospital. Pictured here is the committee of the Grand Chapter Board in action, preparing to spread sunshine and sheer in lives of all the ill and worn.  Standing are, Mrs. Lelia Miller, Mrs. Ernestine Townes, Mrs. Edith Smith, Mrs. Esther Green Smith, Grand Matron.  Seated is Mrs. Carrie V. Smith, chairman of the committee.  The baskets were delivered Sunday, Nov. 8, much to the delight of Woodville patients. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lelia Miller, Ernestine Townes, Edith Smith, Esther Green Smith, and Carrie V. Smith seated on right, assembling food baskets for hospital residents
